name: WIR - Melbourne - Kick Off Meeting
description:
Our initial meeting to kick off the Melbourne chapter of WIR. The agenda will be:

10 minutes - Welcome and introductions - Nicci and Poornima
10 minutes - Discussion about women in STEM and Robotics - Nicci
15 minutes - Andra -  Her career path, Silicon Valley Robotics and how WIR came to be
15 minutes - Sue - Her progression, why we need more women in STEM and how Robotics inspires her as a scientist
10 minutes - Open to discussion

name: WIR - Melbourne - Jan 2021 Meeting
description:
Hello, hello!! Hope everyone had a nice break over the holidays! 

We're looking forward to meeting you all for our January session of WIR. This time we have the pleasure of meeting up with Nicola, Engineering Consultant at Mirragin Unmanned Systems to talk about her career, her foray into STEM and her passion to help young people take their first steps into STEM.

name: WIR - Melbourne - March 2021 Meeting
description:
Hello everyone, hope you're doing well. Things are looking up as we meet Johanna Austin, pilot at PremiAir Helicopters to discuss her experience in the line of her work. Just like all the other women here, she's amazing and passionate about helping people find their way into Robotics. Join us on the 11th of March, 5:30 PM to 6:30 PM, Melbourne time.

name: WIR - Melbourne - April 2021 Meeting
description:
Hello again ladies,

Inviting you all to the April edition of WIRMel. Let me have the honour of introducing Dana Rezazadegan, lecturer of AI and Data Science at Swinburne University of Technology, graduate of QUT, member of Australian Center for Robotic Vision.
